examples.en: The handles on the bag were torn.
The lawyer handles all my affairs.
The car handles well, even on wet roads.
She handles her problems with grace and dignity.
She handles the publicity and all that business.
The finance department handles all the accounts.
At present, the airport handles 110 flights a day.
The airport handles both passenger and cargo flights.
The Post Office handles nearly 2 billion letters and parcels over the Christmas period.
Opposition leaders will be watching carefully to see how the Prime Minister handles the crisis.
